          "title": "IF statements in Excel evaluate a condition and return one value if the condition is <i>true</i> and another value if the condition is <i>false</i>:<br/><code>=IF(condition, value_if_true, value_if_false)</code></br></br>Type the following IF statement that returns the word \"Rich\" if the value in cell B3 is greater than $100,000 and otherwise returns \"Poor\".<br/><code>=IF(B3>100000, \"Rich\", \"Poor\")</code><br/><br/><b>Remember: when writing an Excel formula, text values go inside quotation marks, but numbers do not.</b>",
          "explanation": "",
          "correctAnswer": "<code>=IF(B3>100000, \"Rich\", \"Poor\")</code>",
