          "sourceType": "f",
          "title": "The MEDIAN function in excel returns the median, or middle value in a set of numbers. For example, <code>=MEDIAN(B2:B4)</code> would return 3.8 because if we put the numbers in order, 3.8 would be in the middle.<br/>Type <code>=MEDIAN(B2:B4)</code> to continue.",
